  "time_ut": 1662034089,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bc7\u0bb2\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95 \u0b89\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd  \u0bb5\u0bb4\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcb\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "We look forward to providing further assistance",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "In addition to the $2.9 billion to be provided to Sri Lanka by the International Monetary Fund, the Deputy Head of the International Monetary Fund Mission, Masahiro Nozaki, said that they expect to provide a larger amount. He said that it will be provided through bilateral and multilateral partners of the Monetary Fund.",
        "Greater focus on public financial management, especially prioritizing corruption-free programs should be made mandatory by the government. For that, a strong anti-corruption program should be carried out. He also pointed out the need to reduce the impact of corruption by improving financial transparency and public financial management, introducing a strong anti-corruption legal framework and deepening governance supported by IMF technical assistance.",
        "A change needs to be made in Sri Lanka's tax policy, where tax havens are still at a low level. Increase tax rates on high income earners. He said that it is necessary to create a proper structure."
      ],
